LHASA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Work on a solar-energy power station was completed today and it started generating electricity for a primary school in a suburb of the Tibetan regional capital of Lhasa. 

 A Japanese new energy research and development institute helped the power station as part of solar energy cooperative project between China and Japan to help China's less-developed areas. 

 Tibet has plenty of solar energy resources and Japan has a great deal of experience in the use of solar energy, according to a local official, who says that China and Japan will continue to cooperate in building power projects in Tibet. 

